18:14.580 --> 18:18.100
since the days of the Poles. And today he feels science fiction has produced authors

18:18.100 --> 18:20.340
whose work is as good as anything being written today.

18:20.640 --> 18:22.420
Sturgeon sees another large change too.

18:24.300 --> 18:26.860
The other thing that's happened of course is women.

18:27.780 --> 18:30.940
There have always been women in science fiction. As a matter of fact

18:30.940 --> 18:34.640
somebody who started science fiction as we know it was a woman.

18:35.020 --> 18:38.560
A lady who wrote Frankenstein as she was a teenager.

18:38.940 --> 18:42.060
If I had a time machine I would go back and talk to that lady.

18:43.540 --> 18:46.540
She must have been something else. Amazing woman.

18:46.880 --> 18:50.920
Amazing. I think she was 19 when she wrote Frankenstein.

18:51.880 --> 18:52.660
Mary Shelley.

18:53.520 --> 18:58.500
Mary Shelley published Frankenstein in 1819, some time ago. But Sturgeon goes on to mention

18:58.500 --> 19:01.140
the great number of modern science fiction writers who are women.

19:01.980 --> 19:06.560
The women who have been into science fiction, one of the very best was Judy Merrill.

19:06.960 --> 19:10.760
Back in the 40s he wrote some of the...well if you look in the hall of fame

19:10.760 --> 19:14.120
of science fiction you'll find a Judy Merrill story in there called

19:14.120 --> 19:17.540
That Only a Mother. Which was not only

19:18.640 --> 19:22.420
it was not only a Judy Merrill story but it was the first story she'd ever written.

19:22.820 --> 19:26.100
The first tale she ever made. She told her first story and that was it.

19:26.840 --> 19:29.960
This is an extraordinary story. Really powerful.

19:31.060 --> 19:33.160
Then there are people like I just mentioned.

19:34.200 --> 19:37.740
Then Wild Seed for example is a lovely story.

19:37.940 --> 19:41.840
There's Ursula K. Le Guin who has won a National Book Award.

19:42.760 --> 19:46.060
There's Doris Bacerque who's ideas are always so

19:46.060 --> 19:49.840
totally unexpected. There's Elizabeth Nguyen

19:51.360 --> 19:53.820
who's on and on and on.

19:53.820 --> 19:58.180
There are women in science fiction who are just extraordinary.

19:59.940 --> 20:01.920
There are other ladies in Detroit who said to me that

20:01.920 --> 20:05.860
up to now it's been...the woman

20:05.860 --> 20:09.300
has to work twice as hard and be twice as good as a man

20:09.300 --> 20:13.900
before she can get the same recognition. Then she added, fortunately, that's not

20:13.900 --> 20:16.680
difficult. Which is a great line.

20:27.860 --> 20:28.920
Surgeon believes too

20:28.920 --> 20:31.800
that not only are there a great number of women writers of science fiction

20:31.800 --> 20:33.620
but most of them are superior writers.

20:34.180 --> 20:39.060
But I admire the women in science fiction so very much. Somebody said recently that

20:39.060 --> 20:43.580
there are so many excellent women in science fiction that at long last it's possible to say that they

20:43.580 --> 20:46.320
found a mediocre one. And it has been proved.

20:46.780 --> 20:50.980
It had to be better than the men to get where they are. One of the

20:50.980 --> 20:54.780
great revelations in science fiction, of course, you no problem know about it

20:54.780 --> 20:57.780
was James Tiptree who turns out after having

20:57.780 --> 21:02.980
a shattering success to be a lady by the name of Alice Sheldon.

21:04.080 --> 21:06.520
That was the greatest knowledge for a lot of people.

21:07.260 --> 21:11.120
She kept her head under her wing for so long that altered the room restarted

21:11.120 --> 21:15.940
that she was a CIA man or that she was a collaboration between

21:16.560 --> 21:19.240
Jerry Portell and somebody else or something.

21:20.360 --> 21:22.640
But no sir, she's her own man.

21:23.500 --> 21:25.000
She's good. All of her is good.

21:26.180 --> 21:30.580
This Kate Wilhelm who writes a beautiful steady prose. Very, very good.

21:31.500 --> 21:32.800
That's the name of Night's Wife.

21:34.720 --> 21:38.720
So I'm more pleased than almost anything else about science fiction in that

21:39.080 --> 21:42.800
